{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs32 4. Choosing Which to Use\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Choose Relational (SQL) when: - Your data is structured and relationships are well-defined.\line - You require transactional integrity (e.g., money transfers, invoicing).\line - You need advanced querying and joining of datasets.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Choose NoSQL when: - You handle large-scale, distributed, or unpredictable data.\line - Your schema changes frequently.\line - You prioritize speed and scalability over strict consistency.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Many organizations now use both \u8212- a \u8220"polyglot persistence\u8221" approach \u8212- combining SQL for structured data and NoSQL for scalability or real-time operations.\par}
